Frederic V. Salerno: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 9:32 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Gabelli Entertainment & Telecommunications Acquisition Corp.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Frederic V. Salerno  Chief Executive Officer, Gabelli Entertainment & Telecommunications Acquisition Corp.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 26 different industries.See Board Relationships73--
Background

		Mr. Frederic V. Salerno, also known as Fred, has been the Chief Executive Officer of Gabelli Entertainment & Telecommunications Acquisition Corp. since May 2008. Mr. Salerno serves as an Advisor of Magfusion, Inc. He serves as Senior Advisor of New Mountain Partners III, L.P., New Mountain Partners, L.P., Allegheny New Mountain Partners, L.P. and New Mountain Partners II, L.P. He serves as a Senior Advisor of New Mountain Capital, LLC, where he joined in 2006. From 1997 ... to September 2002, Mr. Salerno served in a variety of senior management positions at Verizon Communications, Inc. He has more than more than 37 years of experience in the telecommunications industry. He served as Vice Chairman and Chief Financial Officer of Verizon Communications Inc. from June 2000 to October 2002. He served as Senior Vice Chairman and Chief Financial Officer of Bell Atlantic Corporation (Verizon’s predecessor) since August 1997 and served in the Office of the Chairman from 1997 to 2001. As a member of the Office of the Chairman, he was responsible for the company's strategic planning efforts, business development and finance as well as oversight of the company's portfolio of international wireline investments. Before the merger of Bell Atlantic and NYNEX Corporation. He served as Vice Chairman, Finance and Business Development of NYNEX from 1994 to 1997. He served as the President of the NYNEX Worldwide Services Group from 1991 to 1994. He was employed at GTE Corporation and Welsh, Carson, Anderson & Stowe. He serves as the Chairman of GGCP, Inc. During his career, Mr. Salerno served as the lead negotiator in three significant mergers: the 1997 merger of Bell Atlantic and NYNEX, Bell Atlantic's merger with GTE and the combination of the U.S. wireless assets of Bell Atlantic and Vodafone into Verizon Wireless. Mr. Salerno joined New York Telephone in 1965. In 1983, Mr. Salerno served as Vice President and directed the divestiture of New York Telephone from the Bell System. Since 1987 until 1991, he served as President and Chief Executive Officer of New York Telephone. He served as Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer of New England Telephone from 1985 to 1987. He has been Chairman of Greenwich PMV Acquisition Corp. since April 2008. He served as Chairman of Genon Power Generation, LLC since April 2000 and LICT Corporation from December 2002 to February 20, 2004. He served as Vice Chairman of NYNEX Corporation since 1994 and served as its Director since 1991. He has been Lead Independent Director at Intercontinental Exchange, Inc. since 2008 and has been its Director since November 2002. He also serves on the board of directors of CBS Broadcasting, Inc. He serves as a Director of Banco Popular North America, Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Akamai Technologies, Inc. since April 2002 and also has been its Lead Director since May 2013. He has been a Director of uPlayMe, Inc. since June 11, 2006 and FCB Financial Holdings, Inc., since October 1, 2010. He has been a Director of Florida Community Bank since July 28, 2010. He has been Director of Associated Capital Group, Inc. since February 8, 2017. He serves as a Director of Stroz Friedberg, LLC. He has been a Director at Magfusion, Inc. since May 14, 2003. He also serves on the boards of multiple NYSE U.S. regulated subsidiaries. He has been Member of Advisory Board at Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. since June 12, 2006. He served as Lead Director of Popular, Inc. until April 28, 2011 and served as its Independent Director from April 2003 to April 28, 2011. He served as Director of Verizon Communications Inc. He served as a Director at LICT from August 2002 to February 20, 2004. He served as Independent Director of Viacom, Inc. since January 1, 2006 until June 16. 2016. He served as a Lead Independent Director of Viacom, Inc. from March 16, 2016 to June 16, 2016. He served as a Director at CBS Corporation from 2007 to May 26, 2016. He served as Director of Keyspan. He served as a Director of National Fuel Gas Company from February 2008 to June 12, 2013. He served as a Director of Banco Popular de Puerto Rico from January 2007 to April 28, 2011. He served as Director of Avnet, Inc. from 1993 to April 1, 2004, GAMCO Investors, Inc. from December 2003 to March 7, 2006, The Dun & Bradstreet Corporation from May 2002 to March 16, 2004 and The Bear Stearns Companies, LLC from 1992 to May 31, 2008. He served as a Director of Heidrick & Struggles International Inc. since May 22, 2003. He served as Director of Consolidated Edison, Inc. from July 2002 to May 21, 2007. He served as Trustee at Consolidated Edison Co. of New York Inc. since July 2002 until May 21, 2007. Mr. Salerno served as Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the State University of New York from 1990 to 1996. An active participant in support of community and educational issues, he is a Trustee of the Inner City Scholarship Fund. He served as Trustee of Manhattan College. He served as Trustee of the Archdiocese of New York’s Partnership for Quality Education. Mr. Salerno has a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from Manhattan College and an MBA from Adelphi University.Read Full Background




