Insider Activity


Individual




Frederic V. Salerno



Mr. Frederic V. Salerno is Independent Director at FCB Financial Holdings, Inc., Independent Director at CBS Corp., Independent Director at Viacom, Inc., Independent Director at Intercontinental Exchange, Inc., Lead Independent Director at Akamai Technologies, Inc., and Chairman at GGCP, Inc. He is on the Board of Directors at FCB Financial Holdings, Inc., Florida Community Bank, NA (Fort Lauderdale, Florida), CBS Corp., Viacom, Inc., Intercontinental Exchange, Inc., Akamai Technologies, Inc., Inner-City Scholarship Fund, Partnerships for Quality Education, Stroz Friedberg LLC, CBS Broadcasting, Inc., ICE US OTC Commodity Markets LLC, Intercontinental Exchange Holdings, Inc, Manhattan College, and Stroz Friedberg, Inc.
Mr. Salerno was previously employed as Independent Director by National Fuel Gas Co., Senior Advisor by Welsh, Carson, Anderson & Stowe, Chairman by Orion Power Holdings, Inc., Vice Chairman & Chief Financial Officer by Bell Atlantic Corp., Vice Chairman-Finance & Business Development by NYNEX Corp., President by Nynex Worldwide Service Group, Inc., Vice Chairman & Chief Financial Officer by Verizon Communications, Inc., Chairman by The State University of New York, President & Chief Executive Officer by New England Telephone & Telegraph Co., and President & Chief Executive Officer by Verizon New York, Inc. He also served on the board at Popular, Inc., Gabelli Asset Management, Inc., GAMCO Investors, Inc., Consolidated Edison, Inc., Viacom, Inc., Avnet, Inc., and Bear, Stearns & Co., Inc.
He received his undergraduate degree from Manhattan College and an MBA from Adelphi University.



